trajectory:
Let $\angle AHB = 137^\circ$ and $\angle ACB = x$.  Then we have that $\angle BAC = 180^\circ - 137^\circ = 43^\circ$, and $\angle AHC = 180^\circ - 43^\circ - x = 137^\circ - x$.  Since $\overline{AX}$ and $\overline{BY}$ are altitudes, we have that $\triangle AHC$ and $\triangle BAH$ are right triangles, so $\angle HAC = 90^\circ$ and $\angle HBA = 90^\circ$.  Then we have that \begin{align*}
\angle HAC + \angle HAB + \angle BAH &= 180^\circ\\
\Rightarrow\quad 90^\circ + (137^\circ - x) + 43^\circ &= 180^\circ\\
\Rightarrow\qquad x &= \boxed{10}.
\end{align*}

