question:
In the diagram, $\triangle ABC$ is right-angled at $C$. Also, points $M$, $N$ and $P$ are the midpoints of sides $BC$, $AC$ and $AB$, respectively.  If the area of $\triangle APN$ is $621\mbox{ cm}^2$, then what is the area, in square centimeters, of $\triangle ABC$? [asy]
size(6cm);
import olympiad;
pair c = (0, 0); pair a = (0, 4); pair n = (0, 2); pair m = (4, 0); pair b = (8, 0); pair p = n + m;
draw(a--b--c--cycle); draw(n--p--m);
draw(rightanglemark(a,c,b));
label("$C$", c, SW); label("$A$", a, N); label("$N$", n, W); label("$M$", m, S); label("$B$", b, E); label("$P$", p, NE);
[/asy]

