\begin{align*}
[ABC]&=\frac{1}{3}[AMN]+\frac{1}{3}[BGN]+\frac{1}{3}[CGN]\\
&=\frac{1}{3}[AMN]+\frac{1}{3}[BGN]+\frac{1}{3}[CGM]\\
&=\frac{1}{3}[AMN]+\frac{1}{3}[BGM]+\frac{1}{3}[AMG].
\end{align*}

Since $AMG$ and $BGM$ are similar triangles, we have that $[BGM]=\frac{1}{3}[AMG].$  Thus,

\begin{align*}
2331&=\frac{1}{3}[AMN]+\frac{1}{3}\left(\frac{1}{3}[AMG]\right)+\frac{1}{3}[AMG]\\
&=\frac{4}{9}[AMG].
\end{align*}

Solving for $[AMG]$, we find that $[AMG]=\frac{2331}{4}=582.75$.  Since $[AMN]=\frac{1}{2}[AMG]$, we have that $[AMN]=\boxed{291.875}$.

