trajectory:
To solve the equation \[\frac{8x+7}{x-3}=9,\] we can start by multiplying both sides of the equation by $x-3$ to get rid of the fraction.

\begin{align*}
\frac{8x+7}{x-3} &= 9\\
\Rightarrow\qquad 8x+7 &= 9(x-3)
\end{align*}Next, we can expand the right side of the equation and collect like terms.

\begin{align*}
8x+7 &= 9x-27\\
\Rightarrow\qquad 8x-9x &= -27-7\\
\Rightarrow\qquad -x &= -34
\end{align*}Now we can solve for $x$ by dividing both sides of the equation by $-1$.

\begin{align*}
-x &= -34\\
\Rightarrow\qquad x &= \boxed{34}
\end{align*}

So, the solution to the equation is $x = 34$.

