trajectory:
We have

\begin{align*}
\begin{vmatrix} a & b & c \\ d & e & f \\ g & h & i \end{vmatrix} & = 567\\
\begin{vmatrix} a & b & c \\ 650d + 972g & 650e + 972h & 650f + 972i \\ -g & -h & -i \end{vmatrix} & =?
\end{align*}

We can use the property of determinants that says if we multiply a row or column by a scalar, we can multiply the determinant by that scalar.

\begin{align*}
\begin{vmatrix} a & b & c \\ 650d + 972g & 650e + 972h & 650f + 972i \\ -g & -h & -i \end{vmatrix} & = \begin{vmatrix} a & b & c \\ d & e & f \\ g & h & i \end{vmatrix} \cdot 650 \cdot 972 \cdot (-1)\\
& = - 650 \cdot 972 \cdot 567 = -317940
\end{align*}

The final answer is $\boxed{-317940}$.

