trajectory:
To evaluate the determinant of the given $3 \times 3$ matrix, we can use the expansion by minors method. We expand along the first row.

\begin{align*}
\begin{vmatrix} 699x & 699\sin \theta & 699\cos \theta \\ -249\sin \theta & -249x & 249 \\ 919\cos \theta & 919 & 919x \end{vmatrix} &= 699x\begin{vmatrix} -249x & 249 \\ 919 & 919x \end{vmatrix} - 699\sin \theta\begin{vmatrix} -249\sin \theta & 249 \\ 919\cos \theta & 919 \end{vmatrix} + 699\cos \theta\begin{vmatrix} -249\sin \theta & -249x \\ 919\cos \theta & 919 \end{vmatrix}
\end{align*}

We can now evaluate the $2 \times 2$ determinants in the expression:

\begin{align*}
&= 699x\left( (-249x)(919x) - (249)(919\cos \theta) \right) - 699\sin \theta\left( (-249\sin \theta)(919) - (249)(919\cos \theta) \right) + 699\cos \theta\left( (-249\sin \theta)(919) - (-249x)(919\cos \theta) \right) \\
&= 699x\left( -227481x - 229071\cos \theta \right) - 699\sin \theta\left( -227481\sin \theta - 229071\cos \theta \right) + 699\cos \theta\left( -227481\sin \theta + 227481x\cos \theta \right) \\
&= -699x(227481x + 229071\cos \theta) + 699\sin \theta(227481\sin \theta + 229071\cos \theta) + 699\cos \theta(-227481\sin \theta + 227481x\cos \theta) \\
&= -699x^2(227481) - 699x(229071)\cos \theta + 699\sin \theta(227481\sin \theta + 229071\cos \theta) - 699\cos \theta(227481\sin \theta - 227481x\cos \theta) \\
&= -158532927x^2 - 160515693x\cos \theta + 699\sin \theta(227481\sin \theta + 229071\cos \theta) - 699\cos \theta(227481\sin \theta - 227481x\cos \theta) \\
&= -158532927x^2 - 160515693x\cos \theta + 160652699\sin^2 \theta + 160652699\sin \theta\cos \theta - 160652699\sin \theta\cos \theta + 160652699x\cos^2 \theta \\
&= -158532927x^2 - 160515693x\cos \theta + 160652699\sin^2 \theta + 160652699x\cos^2 \theta
\end{align*}

Using the identity $\sin^2 \theta + \cos^2 \theta = 1$, we can simplify the expression:

\begin{align*}
-158532927x^2 - 160515693x\cos \theta + 160652699\sin^2 \theta + 160652699x\cos^2 \theta &= -158532927x^2 - 160515693x\cos \theta + 160652699(1 - \cos^2 \theta) + 160652699x\cos^2 \theta \\
&= -158532927x^2 - 160515693x\cos \theta + 160652699 - 160652699\cos^2 \theta + 160652699x\cos^2 \theta \\
&= -158532927x^2 - 160515693x\cos \theta + 160652699 - 160515688x\cos^2 \theta \\
&= -158532927x^2 - 160515693x\cos \theta + 160652699 - 160515688x\cos^2 \theta
\end{align*}

Factoring out $-160515688$ from the last two terms gives

\begin{align*}
-158532927x^2 - 160515693x\cos \theta + 160652699 - 160515688x\cos^2 \theta &= -158532927x^2 - 160515693x\cos \theta + 160515688x\left( \cos \theta - 1 \right) + 160652699 \\
&= -158532927x^2 - 160515693x\cos \theta + 160515688x\cos \theta - 160515688x + 160652699 \\
&= -158532927x^2 - 160515693x\cos \theta + 160515688x\cos \theta - 160515688x + 160652699 \\
&= -158532927x^2 + 160515688x\left( \cos \theta - 1 \right) + 160652699
\end{align*}

Factoring out $-1$ from the first two terms gives

\begin{align*}
-158532927x^2 + 160515688x\left( \cos \theta - 1 \right) + 160652699 &= -1(158532927x^2 - 160515688x\cos \theta + 160652699) \\
&= -\left( 158532927x^2 - 160515688x\cos \theta + 160652699 \right) \\
&= -\begin{vmatrix} 699x & 699\sin \theta & 699\cos \theta \\ -249\sin \theta & -249x & 249 \\ 919\cos \theta & 919 & 919x \end{vmatrix}
\end{align*}

Therefore, the determinant of the original matrix is $\boxed{0}.$

question:
Below is the graph of $y = a \csc bx$ for some positive constants $a$ and $b.$  Find $b.$

[asy]import TrigMacros;

size(500);

real g(real x)
{
	return 2*csc(x/4);
}

draw(graph(g,-8*pi + 0.01, -4*pi - 0.01),red);
draw(graph(g,-4*pi + 0.01,-0.01),red);
draw(graph(g,0.01,4*pi - 0.01),red);
draw(graph(g,4*pi + 0.01,8*pi - 0.01),red);
limits((-8*pi,-5),(8*pi,5),Crop);
draw((-4*pi,-5)--(-4*pi,5),dashed);
draw((4*pi,-5)--(4*pi,5),dashed);
trig_axes(-8*pi,8*pi,-5,5,pi/2,1);
layer();
rm_trig_labels(-15, 15, 2);

label("$1$", (0,1), E);
label("$2$", (0,2), E);
label("$3$", (0,3), E);
label("$4$", (0,4), E);
label("$-1$", (0,-1), E);
label("$-2$", (0,-2), E);
label("$-3$", (0,-3), E);
label("$-4$", (0,-4), E);
[/asy]

